# CSP permissions for fluss.apache.org - Additional allowances to be coordinated with privacy team
# See the CSP request mail for allowing Fluss project to use Algolia, YouTube and Google Calendar:
# https://lists.apache.org/thread/xt0ggzc7f4dj8g91b92w4tk5g8cdslwd
#
# Kapa AI Widget ("Ask AI" button) - domains per Kapa's official CSP guide:
# https://docs.kapa.ai/integrations/faq#how-do-i-fix-csp-errors
#   widget.kapa.ai                     - the widget bundle (script-src)
#   proxy.kapa.ai / *.run.app          - question/answer proxy (connect-src)
#   metrics.kapa.ai                    - widget metrics (connect-src)
#   www.google.com / www.gstatic.com   - reCAPTCHA anti-abuse (script/frame-src)
#   hcaptcha.com / *.hcaptcha.com      - hCaptcha anti-abuse (script/connect/frame-src)
# kapa's own consent screen (data-consent-required) withholds all data from
# its backend until the user consents; see the scripts entry in docusaurus.config.ts.
SetEnv CSP_PROJECT_DOMAINS "https://www.youtube-nocookie.com https://www.youtube.com https://*.algolia.net/ https://*.algolianet.com/ https://*.algolia.io/ https://calendar.google.com https://widget.kapa.ai https://proxy.kapa.ai https://kapa-widget-proxy-la7dkmplpq-uc.a.run.app https://metrics.kapa.ai https://www.google.com https://www.gstatic.com https://hcaptcha.com https://*.hcaptcha.com"